    "description": "Liberty ships were standardized American cargo vessels mass-produced during the Second World War. Designed for rapid, inexpensive construction, they replaced merchant tonnage lost to U-boats and supplied Allied nations through Lend-Lease. Eighteen American shipyards completed 2,710 of the ships between 1941 and 1945 for worldwide wartime service.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Liberty Ship",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liberty%20ship"
      }
    ]
  },
