    "description": "USS Yorktown (CV-5) was the lead ship of the Yorktown-class aircraft carriers. Damaged at the Battle of the Coral Sea, she received emergency repairs in time to fight at Midway in June 1942. Japanese aircraft and submarine torpedoes ultimately left her beyond recovery, and she sank on 7 June.",
