    "description": "USS Saratoga (CV-3) began as a Lexington-class battlecruiser and was converted into an aircraft carrier under the Washington Naval Treaty. She served throughout the Pacific War and survived repeated torpedo attacks. After the war she was expended during Operation Crossroads and sank after the underwater Baker nuclear test.",
