    "description": "Taihō was the Imperial Japanese Navy's first fleet carrier built with an armored flight deck. Commissioned in March 1944, she joined the First Mobile Fleet for the Battle of the Philippine Sea. A torpedo from USS Albacore ruptured aviation-fuel systems, and accumulated vapors later exploded, sinking the carrier on 19 June.",
