    "description": "Taiyō was converted from the passenger liner Kasuga Maru into an escort carrier. Too slow for fleet operations, she primarily trained aircrews, transported aircraft, and escorted convoys. After surviving earlier submarine attacks, she was torpedoed by USS Rasher west of Luzon in August 1944 and sank following a violent aviation-fuel explosion.",
