    "description": "Shin'yō was converted from the German ocean liner Scharnhorst after the ship was trapped in Japan during the war in Europe. Commissioned as an escort carrier in late 1943, she mainly covered convoys and training duties. USS Spadefish torpedoed her in November 1944, causing aviation-fuel explosions that destroyed the ship.",
