    "description": "HMS King George V was the lead ship of Britain's final class of treaty battleships. Armed with ten 14-inch guns, she helped engage Bismarck in May 1941 and later served in the Pacific. She was present in Tokyo Bay for Japan's surrender and remained in service until the early 1950s.",
