    "description": "USS Long Beach (CGN-9) was the world's first nuclear-powered surface combatant and the first purpose-built guided-missile cruiser. Commissioned in 1961, her box-like superstructure carried early phased-array radars. In 1964 she joined Enterprise and Bainbridge for Operation Sea Orbit, circumnavigating the globe without refueling or taking on fuel supplies.",
