    "displayName": "Maury",
    "type": "Destroyer",
    "armaments": [
      {
        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "4x1 127mm/38"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "4x4 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "USS Maury (DD-401) was a Gridley-class destroyer that fought in major carrier battles and later screened Task Force 58 across the Central Pacific. Her service included Coral Sea, Midway, the Eastern Solomons, Leyte, and operations against Japan. Maury earned sixteen battle stars, among the highest totals awarded to a destroyer.",
    "author": "Midnike",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "USN Destroyer MAURY, DD-401",
        "url": "https://www.deviantart.com/midnike/art/USN-Destroyer-MAURY-DD-401-563333362"
      },
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Maury",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS%20Maury%20%28DD-401%29"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "hammann",
    "displayName": "Hammann",
    "type": "Destroyer",
    "armaments": [
      {
        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "4x1 127mm/38"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x4 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "USS Hammann (DD-412) was a Sims-class destroyer that screened carriers at the Battle of the Coral Sea. At Midway she came alongside the damaged USS Yorktown to provide pumps, power, and damage-control support. Torpedoes from the Japanese submarine I-168 struck both ships, breaking Hammann in two and sinking her rapidly.",
    "author": "Midnike",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "USN Destroyer HAMMANN, DD-412",
        "url": "https://www.deviantart.com/midnike/art/USN-Destroyer-HAMMANN-DD-412-563333796"
      },
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Hammann",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS%20Hammann%20%28DD-412%29"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "dewey",
    "displayName": "Dewey",
    "type": "Destroyer",
    "armaments": [
      {
        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "4x1 127mm/38"
      },
      {
        "label": "Anti-aircraft Guns",
        "value": "4x1 20mm/70"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x4 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "USS Dewey (DD-349) was the first Farragut-class destroyer, representing a new generation of American treaty-era destroyers. She served throughout the Pacific, including carrier screening, the Aleutian campaign, and amphibious operations, before later escort work in other theaters. Dewey survived the war and received thirteen battle stars.",
    "author": "Midnike",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "USN Destroyer DEWEY, DD-349",
        "url": "https://www.deviantart.com/midnike/art/USN-Destroyer-DEWEY-DD-349-563332853"
      },
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Dewey",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS%20Dewey%20%28DD-349%29"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "asashio",
    "displayName": "Asashio",
    "type": "Destroyer",
    "armaments": [
      {
        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "3x2 127mm/50 3rd Year Type"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x4 610mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "Asashio was the lead ship of Japan's first large destroyer class designed after withdrawal from treaty limits. Armed with 127 mm guns and Type 93 torpedoes, she combined high speed with strong offensive power. Allied aircraft sank her while she attempted to rescue survivors during the Battle of the Bismarck Sea in March 1943.",
    "author": "Midnike",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Asashio",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese%20destroyer%20Asashio%20%281936%29"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "yugumo",
    "displayName": "Yūgumo",
    "type": "Destroyer",
    "armaments": [
      {
        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "3x2 127mm/50 3rd Year Type"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x4 610mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "Yūgumo was the lead ship of an improved Japanese fleet-destroyer class derived from the Kagerō design. She retained powerful torpedo armament and long range while incorporating modest refinements. During the Battle of Vella Lavella in October 1943, American destroyer gunfire and a torpedo sank her after a close night engagement.",
    "author": "Midnike",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Yūgumo",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese%20destroyer%20Y%C5%ABgumo%20%281941%29"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "yukikaze",
    "displayName": "Yukikaze",
    "type": "Destroyer",
    "armaments": [
      {
        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "3x2 127mm/50 3rd Year Type"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x4 610mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "Yukikaze was a Kagerō-class destroyer famous for surviving many of the Imperial Japanese Navy's most dangerous operations. She fought from the opening Pacific campaigns through Operation Ten-Go. Transferred to the Republic of China after the war and renamed Tan Yang, she remained in service until 1966.",
    "author": "Midnike",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Yukikaze",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese%20destroyer%20Yukikaze%20%281939%29"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
