        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "5x1 127mm/45"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x4 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "Z11 Bernd von Arnim was a German Type 1934A destroyer commissioned in 1938. She participated in the invasion of Norway and landed troops at Narvik. After exhausting much of her ammunition and suffering damage during the Second Battle of Narvik, her crew scuttled the ship in April 1940.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Z11 Bernd von Arnim",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German%20destroyer%20Z11%20Bernd%20von%20Arnim"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
