        "value": "1x5 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "V is a speculative British destroyer design derived from the established V and W-class platform. The proposal emphasizes greater speed, larger boilers, and quadruple torpedo tubes while retaining the compact fleet-destroyer layout. It remained an interwar paper concept rather than a commissioned Royal Navy class.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — V",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V%20and%20W-class%20destroyer"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
