        "label": "Main Battery",
        "value": "3x1 120mm/45"
      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "1x5 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "Y is a speculative further development of Britain's V and W-class destroyer family. The design combines improved endurance and anti-submarine equipment with more modern radar and sonar concepts. It is presented as an artistic paper design and should not be confused with the historical Second World War Y-class destroyers.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — Y",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V%20and%20W-class%20destroyer"
      }
    ]
  },
