        "value": "2x4 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "HMS Ardent was an A-class destroyer commissioned in 1930. She performed fleet and escort duties during the opening months of the Second World War. While escorting the aircraft carrier HMS Glorious off Norway in June 1940, Ardent attacked Scharnhorst and Gneisenau before German gunfire sank her.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
      {
