      },
      {
        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x1 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "PT-791 was a late-production American motor torpedo boat of the Higgins 78-foot family. A wooden hull and three gasoline engines gave boats of this type speeds around 40 knots. Their torpedoes, automatic weapons, and compact size suited night attacks, patrol, escort, and limited anti-submarine missions.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
