        "label": "Torpedoes",
        "value": "2x1 533mm"
      }
    ],
    "description": "The S-100 class was a late-war German Schnellboot design known to the Allies as an E-boat. Its diesel-powered, round-bottomed hull combined high speed with excellent performance in rough seas. Two 533 mm torpedo tubes and increasingly heavy automatic weapons made the type dangerous in coastal waters.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
      {
        "name": "Wikipedia — S-100",
        "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E-boat"
      }
    ]
  },
