      }
    ],
    "description": "MTB-77 was a British motor torpedo boat of the Vosper 72-foot family. Three gasoline engines produced speeds near 40 knots, while torpedoes and light automatic weapons supported night attacks and patrols. Boats of this type operated in the Mediterranean and English Channel on interception, escort, and clandestine missions.",
    "author": "Unknown",
    "links": [
