    "description": "The Soviet Project 183 motor torpedo boat, designated P-6 by NATO, was a wooden-hulled postwar attack craft capable of roughly 45 knots. It carried 533 mm torpedoes, twin 25 mm guns, and depth charges. Large numbers served with the Soviet Navy and were exported to allied states.",
