        "value": "Nonefixed armament"
      }
    ],
    "description": "USNS Mercy (T-AH-19) is the lead ship of the United States Navy's Mercy-class hospital ships. Originally completed in 1976 as the oil tanker SS Worth, she was converted and entered naval service in 1986. Mercy provides afloat medical care, disaster response, and humanitarian assistance from her home port in San Diego.",
