        "value": "Nonefixed armament"
      }
    ],
    "description": "HMHS Britannic was the third Olympic-class ocean liner and a sister ship of Titanic. Requisitioned as a hospital ship during the First World War, she was painted white with large red crosses. Britannic struck a mine in the Aegean Sea in November 1916 and became the largest ship lost during the war.",
